5|$|Leonardo Bruni was {{the first}} to use {{tripartite}} periodization in <b>his</b> <b>History</b> <b>of</b> the Florentine People (1442). Bruni's first two periods were based on those of Petrarch, but he added a third period because he believed that Italy was no longer in a state of decline. Flavio Biondo used a similar framework in Decades of History from the Deterioration of the Roman Empire (1439–1453).|$|E
